node.text: Amy Jackson has built her wardrobe around pre-loved pieces. Looking for clothes that give her the “feel-good factor”, the actor and model knows how to spot a glamorous vintage piece – including a dress previously owned by #PrincessMargaret. From celebrating renowned designers like @StellaMcCartney with an item that is “happiness in a jumper”, to championing new designers like @ClioPeppiatt, watch as Amy talks us through her seven favourite looks.

node.text: As the Olympic spirit sweeps the nation, let former Olympic gymnast Emilie Goldblum guide you through a restorative #WorkoutWednesday. From competing in the 2000 Summer Games in Sydney to performing with #Cher and #TheWeeknd, Emilie has done it all, so she’s no stranger to looking after her body to avoid injuries. Join in as she takes you through a 20 minute stretch session, and tag @BritishVogue in your next #WorkoutWednesday video to let us know where you're taking part.

node.text: The founder of @AnniesIbiza – one of #KateMoss’s go-to stores for rare, one-of-a-kind vintage – Annie Doble takes #BritishVogue through five of her current wardrobe favourites. From a summer-ready silk slip dress to a party dress embellished with feathers and sustainable sequins, and a rare vintage Thierry Mugler rainbow jacket, watch as Annie walks us through her most-loved looks from her Ibiza home.

Directed by @RJGoni.

node.text:
Racing down LA’s Melrose Avenue in the California sun, supermodel #AlessandraAmbrosio takes on Vogue’s latest Shopping Challenge. The goal? She must style three animal-print outfits for three occasions, in just 60 minutes. Watch as she embraces her wild side as she styles a selection of looks for a brunch, job interview and party. 

This episode of The Shopping Challenge was filmed pre-pandemic and before social distancing guidelines were issued.

node.text: “I definitely feel like young girls are being made to grow up far quicker than they are and not celebrating the actual age they are at,” CEO of @BlackGirlFest, @NKrystal_, tells #BritishVogue in the second instalment of @TheOfficialPandora’s speaker series: ‘10 Minutes With’. Watch as the young entrepreneur talks through her inspirations, mentors and how embracing your own uniqueness can be used to your advantage.

node.text:
In a departure from her usual fresh-faced make-up, #ToniGarrn is taking on high-impact red-carpet glamour. “The step that I would never dare to do myself… I’m going to do eyeliner,” says the model. Watch as she demonstrates a bold make-up look that offers instant glamour. 

Directed by @Julia_Muecke.

node.text: It’s a well-known fact that wearing SPF is one of the best ways to protect your skin – but how do you do it right to avoid signs of ageing and pigmentation? Watch as #BritishVogue’s beauty and lifestyle director @JessicaDiner does a sunscreen deep dive with @LaRochePosay dermatologist Dr Hiva Fassihi to discuss how to incorporate SPF into your everyday make-up routine (and why make-up with SPF isn’t enough), the difference between the effects of ultraviolet A and ultraviolet B on your skin, and why it’s important to apply sunscreen even if you’re not leaving the house.

node.title: Face Facts: The Importance Of SPF No Matter The Season

node.text: "When a woman frees herself from the colour bottle, chances are she will not go back. I know I never did!" While once we scrambled to cover any sort of silver, white or grey hair, this is no longer the case – instead, it’s never been chicer. At the link in bio, eight women share their stories about going grey, along with products they love and why it's the most empowering beauty choice one can make.

node.text:
Who says a white wedding gown is your only option? Founder of @Tat.London, @The.Charlie.P married her boyfriend of 10 years in her “fantasy” fuchsia @CarolinaHerrera dress. After rearranging her wedding three times, “Everything else had fallen away… I just wanted to have my best friend become my husband,” she writes. Click the link in bio to read Charlie’s account of the colourful day in full.

Photographed by @WillPatrickWeddings.

node.text:
Looking to step up your beauty game but not sure where to start? We’ve got you covered. To get some inspiration, #BritishVogue asked 20 of the industry’s leading make-up artists for their top summer beauty looks – and they delivered ideas in abundance. From metallic lips to glowing skin, orange blush to graded pinks, click the link in bio for the biggest beauty trends to try this summer.

Make-up by @Diane.Kendal.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by British Vogue on August 14, 2021 tagging @iamkristindavis, @sarahjessicaparker, @kimcattrall, and @cynthiaenixon. May be an image of 4 people and people standing.

node.text: Ahead of the #SexAndTheCity reboot, writer Deborah Linton reflects on the way a best friendship in her 30s changed the course of her life. “The depiction, over six seasons and two movies, of four ostensibly different women, who found their way into the chapters of one another’s lives just when they were needed there, reflects all that I have learned to be true about the friendships that fulfil us most: they may well be among the great loves of our life.” Read her essay in full, at the link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by British Vogue on August 14, 2021. May be an image of 2 people and people standing.

node.text:
Bright pops of colour and eye-catching prints have been dominating the streets during #CopenhagenFashionWeek. Injecting joy through our clothes, aka “dopamine dressing”, has become one of the biggest trends to emerge from the pandemic. At the link in bio, take a look at the most uplifting street-style looks for some inspiration. 

Photographed by @StyleDuMonde.

node.text:
Is there a better, cheesier Hollywood trope than the makeover montage? Comedies and rom-coms love to take a star and give them a splashy new look. From #TheDevilWearsPrada to #PrettyWoman and #Catwoman, click the link in bio for the best Hollywood makeover scenes of all time, ranked. 

‘The Devil Wears Prada’, 2006.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by British Vogue on August 13, 2021. May be an image of 1 person.

node.text: There truly is no better summer beauty muse than #JaneBirkin. Whether it’s the fringe that has inspired countless imitations or those defined eyelashes, her minimal approach to beauty is summer incarnate. At the link in bio enjoy her tousled lengths, mussed-up fringe and freckled skin in #BritishVogue’s edit of Birkin’s best beach-ready moments.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by British Vogue on August 13, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, standing and outdoors.

node.text:
As the first female Prime Minister of Barbados, history-making @MaMottley has monumental plans. The charismatic force for change talks to @GaryYounge about leading the country towards republicanism and shaking off its colonial past in the September 2021 issue of #BritishVogue. See the full story in the new issue and at the link in bio now.

#MiaMottley photographed by @KyleBabb, with production by @ShakeProductionsNYC.

node.text: Amy Jackson has built her wardrobe around pre-loved pieces. Looking for clothes that give her the “feel-good factor”, the actor and model knows how to spot a glamorous vintage piece – including a dress previously owned by #PrincessMargaret. From celebrating renowned designers like @StellaMcCartney with an item that is “happiness in a jumper”, to championing new designers like @ClioPeppiatt, watch as Amy talks us through her seven favourite looks.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by British Vogue on August 12, 2021 tagging @cindycrawford. May be an image of 1 person and standing.

node.text: Since she burst onto the catwalk as one of the original supers, #CindyCrawford has inspired countless trends. Now, with ’90s style back with a vengeance, people are turning to the super as the ultimate beauty muse. The latest look the masses are imitating? Her signature voluminous blow dry and "money pieces" highlights, which were always enviably on point. Click the link in bio to take a look at some of Crawford’s very best larger-than-life ’90s hairstyles to inspire your next look.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by British Vogue on August 12, 2021 tagging @florencepugh. May be an image of 1 person and outdoors.

node.text: Period drama lovers, listen up. After making her @Marvel debut in #BlackWidow, #FlorencePugh is back in period drama mode. Behold: your first look at the actor as nurse Lib Wright, in @NetflixUK’s adaptation of @E_Donoghue’s ‘The Wonder’. Click the link in bio for everything you need to know about the new film.

node.text: From slinky, ’90s-esque slips to dreamy daytime options, there was plenty of summer dress inspiration on the SS21 runways. Fresh takes on the trusty LBD were seen across the board, which #HaileyBieber has already applied to her date-night outfits. #JenniferLopez, meanwhile, has been adding mood-boosting rays of colour to her wardrobe. Click the link in bio for the nine summer dress trends to try now.
